<p>
  HealthTap partnered with a global healthcare organization to create a holistic, interactive system between the care provider and patients. Care plans is a method for doctors to help patients stay healthy after they leave their office by keeping track of things like prescribed medicine intake and interjecting if patients fall of rails. Interjections can be as simple as a reminder to take medication. Or it can be as complex and multi-faceted as a guideline for diabetic patients to follow based on their blood glucose readings.
</p>

<h2>Problem</h2>
<p>
  In order to provide continuous care, doctors need a tool to create this care journey. This tool needs to provide a set of actionable items for patients to follow and a set of rules that define what actions to follow. This is the <b>authoring</b> part of care plans.
