<p>
  These actions and triggers can have endless number of types. Yet, we wanted to focus on a small set of necessities first. Our goal wasn’t to conquer all fields of medicine; our goal was to focus on a small number of conditions first, strengthen that, and expand from there. Hence, we limited the number of action and trigger types. We also learned that there is no such “onesize-fits-all” model when it comes to Care Plans. Each plan must be modified per patient’s health records. For example, ways to manage type II diabetes are very, very different for a man in his 60s and a pregnant mom in her 30s.
</p>

