<p>
  After the new direction was signed off, I worked closely with our team and the doctors to crystalize the design. I also learned that the user group I’m targeting is very different from what I assuemd. Because doctors work in such tight schedule and are used to the clunky, slow softwares, they preferred things to be bigger, bolder, and more obvious. For instance, they always preferred color-coding and highlighting clickable areas.
</p>


<h2>Final Design</h2>
<p>
  The most important part of the final design was the visualization of the Care Plan. Essentially, Care Plan is a personalized and guided map for a patient’s journey in combating or managing a condition. It was important for the author to understand how the actions and triggers are connected; “X” behavior of a patient will trigger “Y” actions.
</p>

